From 905a51bddc80e0803beba618f0274950f2c8edac Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 24 May 2026 09:03:25 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(ml): dual-head LSTM for trend direction + strength
 prediction

Extend the LSTM pipeline from price-only regression into a multi-task
model that predicts both USD prices and trend direction/strength.

Model changes (model.py):
- Add DirectionHead: Linear(128->64)->ReLU->Dropout->Linear(64->horizon*3)
  output shape (batch, 7, 3) - raw logits for DOWN/FLAT/UP per day
- LSTMModel gains use_direction_head + n_classes params
- Dual-head forward() returns (price_preds, dir_logits) tuple
- Single-head mode (use_direction_head=False) fully backward-compatible

Feature engineering (preprocess.py): 5 -> 9 input features
- macd_norm: (EMA12-EMA26)/close - trend momentum
- bb_pct_b: (close-lower)/(upper-lower) - mean-reversion signal
- atr_norm: proxy ATR via |log_return_1d|*close / close (no H/L in CSV)
- fear_greed: Crypto Fear & Greed Index /100 (free API, fallback 0.5)
  backed by arXiv:2102.08189 (+5-20% directional accuracy)
- New make_direction_labels() function: std-relative threshold for
  DOWN(0)/FLAT(1)/UP(2) labels
- load_and_preprocess() now returns 11-tuple (adds y_dir splits)

Training (train_lstm.py):
- Combined loss: alpha*HuberLoss(prices) + beta*CrossEntropyLoss(dirs)
  (HuberLoss is more robust than MSE for fat-tailed financial returns)
- --alpha and --beta CLI flags (default 1.0 / 0.5)
- compute_metrics() adds direction_accuracy_pct and f1_macro
- Saves model as lstm_{coin}_v2.pt

Inference (inference.py):
- _mimo_predict_full(): single forward pass yields prices + directions
- direction: UP/FLAT/DOWN per forecast day
- direction_prob: softmax confidence (replaces static 0.8)
- trend_strength: STRONG/MODERATE/WEAK from |log_return| vs training sigma
- Graceful v2->v1 model fallback
- MongoDB doc gains direction, direction_prob, trend_strength fields

Dashboard (03_prediction.py):
- Trend Direction & Strength section below price chart
- up/flat/down arrows with strength color indicators per day
- Summary counts shown when >=2 days agree on direction

API (main.py):
- /api/predictions/{coin} response includes direction + trend fields

Tests (test_lstm.py): 51/51 pass
- TestDirectionHead (3 tests): shape, softmax, dtype
- TestDirectionLabels (6 tests): shape, valid values, threshold logic
- TestMultiTaskModel (6 tests): dual/single-head outputs
- TestNewPreprocessReturnShape (4 tests): 11-tuple, y_dir shapes/values

Research references:
- arXiv:2603.16886 (2026): 54-60% dir acc with OHLCV+indicators
- arXiv:2102.08189 (2021): Fear & Greed -> 67-84% dir acc
- arXiv:2512.22326 (2025): exogenous features > architecture choice

